  "formula": "1d100",
  "description": "<p>Use this oracle to identify the shape of the array of cylinders that compose a habitat cluster. Knucklebones, pyramids, and cubes might be grouped with others. If the shape is determined to be any of these, roll &gt;Array Quantity to determine the amount of arrays in the habitat cluster. Then, for each additional array, roll on this table again and reroll the \"Rungworld, \"Sphere\", and \"Topopolis\" results.</p>",
